and you get to learn who you are.

15
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:56,950
Prosecutor Cha.

16
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:57,992
Are you okay?

17
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,753
You woke up after three days.

18
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:10,547
Three days?

19
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,090
The bullet pierced your shoulder.

20
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:15,343
If it hit you a bit higher,
it would've been a disaster.

21
00:02:16,052 --> 00:02:17,387
Thank goodness.

22
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:20,723
By the way, why are you…

23
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:25,061
Noh Tae-nam detonated a grenade.

24
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:26,354
A grenade?

25
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,857
Are you okay?

26
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:29,983
I was lucky.

27
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,610
But Noh Tae-nam…

28
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,618
has shards stuck in his body,

29
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,662
and he's still unconscious.

30
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:46,916
The doctor says
he has a very low chance of making it.

31
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,414
I'm sure Adjutant Yang

32
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:29,542
was ordered by Noh Hwa-young to kill you.

33
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:38,593
Who was it?

34
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:40,970
Who did this to you?

35
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:43,640
I'm okay. Don't worry.

36
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:44,974
Adjutant Yang did this.

37
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,517
Noh Hwa-young's adjutant?

38
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:48,311
Did Noh Hwa-young instigate this?

39
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,482
We should put out
an APB on Adjutant Yang first…

40
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:53,858
No.

41
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:56,277
When I leave the hospital,

42
00:03:56,361 --> 00:03:57,528
I will find Adjutant Yang

43
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:59,739
-and persuade her, too.
-Woo-in.

44
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:03,993
Adjutant Yang may remain silent forever
and take all the blame.

45
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:07,705
Prosecutor Cha, you take
on Adjutant Yang until the end.

46
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:09,165
Yes, sir.

47
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:13,586
Prosecutor Doh, did you tell Woo-in?

48
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:16,589
Tell me what?

49
00:04:18,716 --> 00:04:20,677
The X-files of the Patriotic Society…

50
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,053
We got them.

51
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:36,776
What happened to Cha Woo-in?

52
00:04:36,859 --> 00:04:38,611
Where is Adjutant Yang Jong-sook?

53
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,072
Why are you asking me that?

54
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,162
Did you make that face 20 years ago, too?

55
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,165
When you killed my parents

56
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,376
and got away?

57
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,466
-Watch what you say, Doh Bae-man.
-You…

58
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:02,468
What?

59
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:04,512
You will never be able to get out

60
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:06,556
of the hell you created yourself.

61
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:26,868
Boss.

62
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:29,078
We're doomed.

63
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:30,121
WANTED SUSPECTS

64
00:05:30,204 --> 00:05:31,414
What the heck is this?

65
00:05:32,248 --> 00:05:34,417
I thought he was a nobleman,

66
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:37,879
but he turned out to be a nobody.

67
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,930
All three of us are wanted.

68
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,557
Wanted?

69
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:51,893
WANTED SUSPECTS

70
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:53,603
My company…

71
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:55,688
Seolak Cheonji!

72
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,982
It has been completely smashed!

73
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:03,404
Prosecutor Cha!

74
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:05,073
Staff Judge Advocate.

75
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:07,325
Subsection Chiefs.

76
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,662
The Staff Judge Advocate prepared this.

77
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,081
And I paid for it.

78
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:15,541
We were just so shocked.

79
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,211
I didn't know you'd come.

80
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:20,213
Thank you for coming.

81
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,801
I heard you got shot. Right?

82
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:26,219
Who shot you?

83
00:06:26,302 --> 00:06:27,553
Who was it?

84
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,263
I heard you saw the culprit's face!

85
00:06:29,347 --> 00:06:31,057
So why aren't you telling us?

86
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:36,437
You can trust me. Now tell me who it is.

87
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:46,781
I will tell you as I prepare for
Division Commander Noh Hwa-young's trial.

88
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:53,496
It has something to do
with the Division Commander?

89
00:06:58,251 --> 00:06:59,836
Come.

90
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:14,225
Hurry!

91
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:22,650
What the heck?

92
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:26,195
Didn't Noh Tae-nam survive
the mass shooting?

93
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,864
That's what I heard, too.

94
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:31,075
We snuck in here,
so we can't just ask a nurse.

95
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:34,787
Hey, wake up, kid.

96
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:36,122
You know it, right?

97
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,416
-Where are the X-files?
-You idiot.

98
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:40,877
He's obviously in a coma!
He won't wake up like that!

99
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,462
But we have to find the files!

100
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,506
And I lost my stock!
I can't be sane right now!

101
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,957
Are you leaving the hospital already?

102
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:23,252
The doctor says
I need to stay here longer,

103
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,879
but I've got no time.

104
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:29,550
And the 90 days I promised you
are really coming to an end.

105
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,011
I'll join you soon, too.

106
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:37,308
Yong Moon-goo came here last night.

107
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:40,394
Did you see Yong Moon-goo and lose him?

108
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,355
I didn't lose him. I let him go.

109
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:47,360
I have plans, so Military Prosecutor Cha,

110
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:49,820
please just focus on recovering.

111
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,449
That's the right attitude for reporting.

112
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:59,163
The X-files of the Patriotic Society
your father left

113
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:03,251
went around and around
and came back to you.

114
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:06,546
He'd lived his life
more fiercely than I knew.

115
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:10,591
How did he investigate
and find out all those?

116
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:14,512
Perhaps the revenge my father wants

117
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:19,392
is me completing
what he wasn't able to complete.

118
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:25,314
I need someone to verify
the details in these files.

119
00:09:26,148 --> 00:09:27,650
Who can verify the corruption

120
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,403
between the Patriotic Society
and the defense companies.

121
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:33,614
The one whom we chose to use as bait.

122
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,534
Vice Corps Commander Heo Kang-in.

123
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:49,005
Doh Bae-man,
where and how did you get this?

124
00:09:49,088 --> 00:09:51,674
Isn't it amazing?

125
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:54,802
The corruption
of the rotten defense industry

126
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:58,639
that conspired with the Patriotic Society
is all neatly organized.

127
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,891
I don't know anything about it!

128
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:03,644
Your reaction is proof
that you know very well about it.

129
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:08,691
I won't admit it!
I won't suffer in the Minister's place!

130
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:12,069
Most guilty people yell like you.

131
00:10:12,653 --> 00:10:14,572
And they bark when they're scared.

132
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:17,533
What? Doh Bae-man, you bastard!

133
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,754
Can't you

134
00:10:29,837 --> 00:10:34,258
just let me go on condition
that I take my uniform off?

135
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:39,013
You must be punished
for what you did in your uniform.

136
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:43,517
I only followed orders!

137
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:44,560
You know that!

138
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,812
You can't help it
if you're a serviceperson!

139
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,153
Then I can promise you this one thing.

140
00:10:55,571 --> 00:10:56,864
What is it?

141
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:02,119
I will make sure
that you won't be punished

142
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,579
for what you didn't do.

143
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:06,707
It was all ordered
by Minister Lee Jae-sik, anyway.

144
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:07,708
Of course!

145
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,920
I have no power
to make decisions on my own!

146
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:13,422
The Minister made all of the decisions!

147
00:11:14,256 --> 00:11:16,175
That expression you just made is great.

148
00:11:16,258 --> 00:11:19,553
Please do that during the trial
for Minister Lee Jae-sik, too.

149
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,972
That expression is great.

150
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:31,941
Vice Corps Commander Heo Kang-in
is going to testify.

151
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,152
Wow, this…

152
00:11:35,903 --> 00:11:38,280
became like five times bigger
than its initial size.

153
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:41,492
That's why I called it a gate.

154
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:48,165
I'm not going to destroy

155
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:51,419
Minister Lee with just
the corruption of the defense industry.

156
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:54,922
You provide the investigation information
and help me with the trial.

157
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:56,215
Prosecutor Doh.

158
00:11:56,298 --> 00:12:00,302
I did hear that you're like a Doberman,
and you sure do your job like that.

159
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:04,932
Is the preparation for Division Commander
Noh Hwa-young's trial going well?

160
00:12:05,015 --> 00:12:06,142
Of course.

161
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:08,644
I'm making Yong Moon-goo move.

162
00:12:08,727 --> 00:12:11,689
But he doesn't know
that he's being forced to move.

163
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:24,243
Are you keeping Medical Officer
Jo Soo-chan safe?

164
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:27,329
Yes. But why?

165
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:32,001
That medical officer
is the only card we have now.

166
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,628
I'll use him to negotiate with Noh.

167
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:40,676
Noh Hwa-young's trial will begin soon.

168
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:44,221
The only charge Doh
can apply to her in court

169
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,599
is failure to frustrate
the crimes of subordinates.

170
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:49,935
He can't even scratch her
with just that charge.

171
00:12:50,686 --> 00:12:54,565
I'm sure he will collect
all possible charges and integrate them.

172
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:02,490
Where is the medical officer?

173
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,950
We put him in a pawn shop.

174
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:06,952
A pawn shop?

175
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:10,748
You know that pawn shops deal
with all kinds of things.

176
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:15,127
That pawn shop deals with people too.

177
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:21,217
I see.

178
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,427
We'll take off as soon as the sun rises.

179
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:32,770
You left the hospital already?
But your wound hasn't even healed yet.

180
00:13:32,853 --> 00:13:35,272
Lying in bed doesn't suit me.

181
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:36,565
You're just so…

182
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,734
Right.

183
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:40,986
Yong Moon-goo began to move.

184
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:43,447
Now I just need to sit and watch.

185
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:45,074
I'll look forward to it.

186
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:14,812
You did many things
with this thing on your head, Cha Woo-in.

187
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,277
You're just like your father.

188
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:26,407
Both he and you threatened me terribly
solely based on your belief.

189
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,701
If my father considered you
someone special,

190
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:33,372
I'm sure he tried
to stop you from going berserk.

191
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:37,293
Are you still concerned about that?

192
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,420
You're very naive.

193
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:43,924
Your father and I didn't have
any type of relationship.

194
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:47,678
This time, you survived
because you were lucky,

195
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:50,723
but you may end up like your father soon.

196
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:55,895
Because I get rid of everything
that gets in my way.

197
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:05,279
You use your subordinate's loyalty to you.

198
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,656
How long will you be able to do that?

199
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:08,657
My subordinate?

200
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:11,368
That idiot
who couldn't even get rid of you?

201
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:14,788
She's just my tool.

202
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:16,582
Though she's useless now.

203
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:21,378
Now I can put bullets
into your head myself.

204
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,631
Come anytime.

205
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:24,924
I'll be waiting.

206
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:30,095
If you knew my father well,
then you should know how I am too.

207
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:33,682
Your end…

208
00:15:34,516 --> 00:15:36,143
is coming soon.

209
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:38,062
Noh Hwa-young.

210
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,879
Those pawn shop bastards.

211
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:08,133
They should keep the item
in its initial condition.

212
00:16:08,217 --> 00:16:09,343
This is totally damaged!

213
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:10,970
Bring him.

214
00:16:29,613 --> 00:16:30,864
So this jerk will be

215
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:34,994
the item for you to start
the second round of your life, right?

216
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:37,788
I want to barge
into the Division Commander's office

217
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:40,958
and make a deal with Noh Hwa-young,
and it’s hard to wait.

218
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:46,255
By the way, since you've been staying,
eating, and sleeping with us,

219
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:48,298
we must've rubbed off on you.

220
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,968
Your style is becoming similar to ours.

221
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:51,969
Let's go.

222
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:01,895
Doh Bae-man.

223
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:04,857
Wow, this tracking device is great.

224
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:07,026
I think it's ready
to be released as a product.

225
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:11,572
Will you be okay all by yourself?
They seem to be outnumbering you.

226
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:13,657
Outnumbering…

227
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:17,077
There are only two of them
I need to fight.

228
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,038
Hey, Yong Moon-goo can't fight.

229
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,711
Hey, Kang Ha-joon, did you…

230
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:29,006
put a tracking device on my car, too?

231
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:30,716
Where are you?

232
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:33,510
You know what?

233
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:36,096
Tricking a trickster

234
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,890
is twice as joyful.

235
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,768
And when I asked if you'd be okay,

236
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:43,020
I was asking if you'd be okay
without Woo-in.

237
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:47,024
But I don't think it'll be helpful
to have you here,

238
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:48,150
Kang Ha-joon.

239
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:55,157
It's a bias if you think
I can't fight, Doh Bae-man.

240
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:02,956
Gosh.

241
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,263
My foot!

242
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:35,322
Gosh, it hurts.

243
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:39,326
Go.

244
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:45,582
Where do you think you're going?

245
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:52,089
Hey.

246
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:53,215
Doh Bae-man.

247
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,434
Hey!

248
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:14,403
The end.

249
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,078
You should be good!

250
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:24,496
Shut up!

251
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:26,206
Detective?

252
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:27,708
What?

253
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,919
May I say my last farewell

254
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,671
to the wanted suspect?

255
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:36,175
Be quick.

256
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,266
The last farewell?

257
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:46,977
I've always been consistent.

258
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:48,770
You're the one who betrayed me.

259
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:51,064
The X-files of the Patriotic Society…

260
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,734
