We checked your voice left
at the report center.

519
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:15,840
Your hesitant face
when you aimed your gun at me.

520
00:36:15,923 --> 00:36:19,135
The frightened voice from making a report.

521
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:21,971
You didn't have any intention to kill me.

522
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:28,060
Listen carefully, Adjutant Yang Jong-sook.

523
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:30,521
With the help of the Division Commander,

524
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:32,899
you revealed your trauma
from the past to the world

525
00:36:32,982 --> 00:36:35,526
and made the Corps Commander get punished.

526
00:36:36,402 --> 00:36:39,280
And you thanked me.

527
00:36:40,656 --> 00:36:43,701
You didn't have any reason
or motive to shoot me.

528
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:47,914
Let me bring a charge
against Division Commander Noh Hwa-young,

529
00:36:47,997 --> 00:36:51,792
the real culprit who fired the gun
by hiding behind you.

530
00:37:10,811 --> 00:37:12,146
My subordinate?

531
00:37:12,230 --> 00:37:14,482
That idiot
who couldn't even get rid of you?

532
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:16,859
She's just my tool.

533
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:19,111
Though she's useless now.

534
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:23,658
Now I can put bullets
into your head myself.

535
00:37:27,161 --> 00:37:29,747
Even if you take the blame
for what he did,

536
00:37:29,830 --> 00:37:31,082
other servicepeople

537
00:37:31,165 --> 00:37:33,542
will hold guns upon
the Division Commander's orders.

538
00:37:34,126 --> 00:37:37,713
That tragedy of being used,
being thrown out, and being replaced

539
00:37:37,797 --> 00:37:38,839
will continue endlessly

540
00:37:39,382 --> 00:37:42,093
as long as Noh Hwa-young
is wearing a military uniform.

541
00:37:45,972 --> 00:37:50,017
Please help us break that cycle
so other servicepeople

542
00:37:51,185 --> 00:37:53,062
wouldn't be sacrificed

543
00:37:54,605 --> 00:37:55,773
for unfair orders.

544
00:37:58,109 --> 00:37:59,568
I beg you.

545
00:38:01,404 --> 00:38:03,114
This is a recording of a conversation

546
00:38:03,197 --> 00:38:04,991
between Won Ki-choon and Noh Hwa-young.

547
00:38:07,118 --> 00:38:10,538
There was a witness
among our Search Battalion members.

548
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:12,832
He said he'll call all of the reporters

549
00:38:12,915 --> 00:38:14,667
and expose everything.

550
00:38:14,750 --> 00:38:17,169
If that gets revealed, I'm dead.

551
00:38:17,253 --> 00:38:18,671
Let's talk later.

552
00:38:18,754 --> 00:38:20,965
Division Commander!

553
00:38:21,048 --> 00:38:24,135
It also looks like Doh Bae-man figured out

554
00:38:24,218 --> 00:38:25,970
you cut my leg off.

555
00:38:26,053 --> 00:38:27,305
Objection!

556
00:38:27,388 --> 00:38:29,598
It's a one-sided claim
from the dead victim.

557
00:38:30,182 --> 00:38:34,395
In the recording, the defendant
didn't agree or say yes to anything.

558
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:35,980
Sustained.

559
00:38:36,063 --> 00:38:39,692
I'd like to summon a witness who can
prove the credibility of this recording.

560
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:42,903
The prosecution's witness,
please come forward.

561
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:55,583
WITNESS

562
00:38:57,543 --> 00:39:00,504
Is that recording we just heard true?

563
00:39:04,717 --> 00:39:05,968
It's true.

564
00:39:06,052 --> 00:39:07,428
And how do you know?

565
00:39:07,511 --> 00:39:10,598
I was at the scene where
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon's leg

566
00:39:10,681 --> 00:39:11,807
was being cut off.

567
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:17,355
I was called in to suture the leg
after it was cut off.

568
00:39:18,814 --> 00:39:23,235
At first, the Division Commander
ordered Adjutant Yang Jong-sook to do it.

569
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,322
But when Adjutant Yang hesitated,

570
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:29,408
the Division Commander…

571
00:39:31,118 --> 00:39:32,953
cut off the leg of

572
00:39:34,663 --> 00:39:36,415
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon.

573
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:44,632
I rest my case
with the examination of the witness.

574
00:39:47,134 --> 00:39:49,512
Defense Attorney,
please conduct a cross examination.

575
00:39:50,971 --> 00:39:52,348
Your Honor.

576
00:39:52,431 --> 00:39:56,102
May I say something
about Medical Officer Jo Soo-chan?

577
00:39:56,185 --> 00:39:57,478
Go ahead.

578
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:02,108
Captain Jo Soo-chan.

579
00:40:03,317 --> 00:40:06,195
When you were working
at the military hospital,

580
00:40:06,278 --> 00:40:08,781
you went AWOL
for more than a month, correct?

581
00:40:08,864 --> 00:40:10,366
That was--

582
00:40:10,449 --> 00:40:11,409
And

583
00:40:11,492 --> 00:40:15,413
you received warnings from the superiors
due to your gambling charges.

584
00:40:16,622 --> 00:40:19,708
Who would ever trust such a serviceperson
who lacks military spirit?

585
00:40:19,792 --> 00:40:20,668
Your Honor.

586
00:40:20,751 --> 00:40:23,421
The defendant is accusing the witness
with claims

587
00:40:23,504 --> 00:40:25,423
that have nothing to do with this case.

588
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:27,049
Sustained.

589
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:28,717
Defendant, please be cautious.

590
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:33,264
Defense. Do you have
more cross examinations to do?

591
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:37,810
I don't.

592
00:40:37,893 --> 00:40:40,646
We will now move on
to the examination of the next witness.

593
00:40:40,729 --> 00:40:44,900
The prosecution,
is Adjutant Yang Jong-sook present?

594
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,906
If she's not present…

595
00:41:03,210 --> 00:41:04,420
You're here, Cha Woo-in.

596
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:30,154
Your Honor.

597
00:41:31,405 --> 00:41:34,450
She's First Lieutenant Yang Jong-sook,
Division Commander Noh's adjutant.

598
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:39,079
She's a crucial witness who will prove
many of the defendant's crimes.

599
00:41:44,835 --> 00:41:46,462
Noh Hwa-young said that

600
00:41:46,545 --> 00:41:49,423
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon
made a confession.

601
00:41:50,216 --> 00:41:51,342
Is it true?

602
00:41:51,425 --> 00:41:55,304
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon
never made a confession.

603
00:41:56,931 --> 00:41:58,432
How can you be so sure?

604
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:03,062
He actually threatened
the Division Commander.

605
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:05,397
You, Noh Hwa-young,

606
00:42:05,481 --> 00:42:07,900
Corps Commander Hong Moo-seob,
and Lee Jae-sik too…

607
00:42:07,983 --> 00:42:10,027
I have a bomb that will blow all of you.

608
00:42:11,403 --> 00:42:13,531
Now, your fates

609
00:42:13,614 --> 00:42:15,032
are up to me.

610
00:42:15,616 --> 00:42:18,911
How did the defendant act
after she was threatened?

611
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:27,336
She made a decision that's so like her.

612
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:30,756
She…

613
00:42:31,257 --> 00:42:33,342
pulled the trigger of the gun herself.

614
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:48,566
Are you saying that she killed
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon?

615
00:42:49,441 --> 00:42:50,693
Yes.

616
00:42:52,069 --> 00:42:53,779
On that day, the defendant fabricated

617
00:42:53,862 --> 00:42:55,990
the record of entry
and exit for her alibi,

618
00:42:56,073 --> 00:42:58,742
and the witness worked on the fabrication.

619
00:43:00,494 --> 00:43:02,454
I'd like to submit the evidence.

620
00:43:12,047 --> 00:43:13,048
And,

621
00:43:14,049 --> 00:43:15,301
there's one more.

622
00:43:18,053 --> 00:43:19,388
Witness.

623
00:43:19,471 --> 00:43:20,973
Are you sure

624
00:43:21,056 --> 00:43:22,725
you can say it?

625
00:43:28,230 --> 00:43:29,607
Yes.

626
00:43:31,233 --> 00:43:32,818
The Division Commander…

627
00:43:35,112 --> 00:43:38,449
also ordered me to kill you,
Military Prosecutor Cha Woo-in.

628
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:50,085
That'll be all.

629
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:06,268
Now, last but not least, the card to
completely destroy Noh Hwa-young is here.

630
00:44:17,446 --> 00:44:19,198
Are you that happy about it?

631
00:44:19,281 --> 00:44:20,199
Yes.

632
00:44:20,282 --> 00:44:24,578
You got sentenced to 15 years,
with more trials to come,

633
00:44:26,246 --> 00:44:27,998
and you look great in that.

634
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,878
What did I do so wrong to you?

635
00:44:33,379 --> 00:44:36,799
I have nothing to do with your parents'
murder. It was all Noh's doing.

636
00:44:39,468 --> 00:44:42,137
What about President Cha Ho-chul's death?

637
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:46,892
As the prosecutor in charge,
you fabricated the case,

638
00:44:46,975 --> 00:44:49,061
framed him for false charges,

639
00:44:49,144 --> 00:44:51,230
and planned
Won Ki-choon's press conference

640
00:44:51,313 --> 00:44:53,899
and his testimony in court.

641
00:44:53,982 --> 00:44:57,152
That was all.
I didn't do anything more than that.

642
00:44:57,236 --> 00:44:58,320
Okay.

643
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:01,323
I heard you're preparing for an appeal.

644
00:45:02,908 --> 00:45:04,076
This time, I will make

645
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:07,538
an offer you can't refuse.

646
00:45:19,341 --> 00:45:22,719
I'd like to summon a witness
for the charge of instigation of murder

647
00:45:22,803 --> 00:45:24,930
of President Cha Ho-chul six years ago.

648
00:45:25,013 --> 00:45:27,599
It's former CEO Yong Moon-goo
of IM Defense Industry.

649
00:45:40,821 --> 00:45:42,489
Objection!

650
00:45:42,573 --> 00:45:44,950
The witness is currently serving time

651
00:45:45,033 --> 00:45:47,202
and had a big fight with the defendant.

652
00:45:47,286 --> 00:45:49,830
He has a high chance
of committing perjury out of spite.

653
00:45:49,913 --> 00:45:52,875
The witness volunteered to attend
to correct his wrongdoings

654
00:45:52,958 --> 00:45:54,877
from his days as a prosecutor.

655
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:58,630
Please take the witness' brave choice
into consideration, Your Honor.

656
00:45:59,381 --> 00:46:01,133
I will summon the witness.

657
00:46:01,216 --> 00:46:02,509
Please be seated.

658
00:46:13,479 --> 00:46:16,356
Were you the prosecutor
in charge of the case

659
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:19,401
in which President Cha Ho-chul
of IM Defense was involved in?

660
00:46:19,485 --> 00:46:20,652
Yes.

661
00:46:20,736 --> 00:46:24,990
Was Noh Hwa-young, the defendant,
involved in the case?

662
00:46:25,073 --> 00:46:27,993
Yes, she was definitely involved
in the case.

663
00:46:29,828 --> 00:46:31,497
Definitely.

664
00:46:31,580 --> 00:46:33,957
Please tell us the details
of that situation.

665
00:46:35,209 --> 00:46:37,836
I was ordered by Noh Hwa-young.

666
00:46:38,504 --> 00:46:41,715
She ordered me to frame
President Cha Ho-chul for corruption

667
00:46:41,798 --> 00:46:43,342
and to fabricate the case.

668
00:46:43,425 --> 00:46:44,551
So,

669
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:45,886
did you cooperate?

670
00:46:47,095 --> 00:46:48,180
Yes.

671
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:51,975
I drank from the poisoned chalice
for a guaranteed future.

672
00:46:53,227 --> 00:46:54,228
Your Honor.

673
00:46:54,311 --> 00:46:57,231
I hereby submit the evidence
related to that testimony.

674
00:47:06,114 --> 00:47:07,157
Witness.

675
00:47:08,033 --> 00:47:10,577
Do you have evidence related
to the instigation of murder?

676
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:12,829
The conversation
between me and the defendant

677
00:47:12,913 --> 00:47:15,499
are on the phone I used at that time.

678
00:47:16,250 --> 00:47:18,460
I will submit it
right after the trial is over.

679
00:47:19,127 --> 00:47:21,672
So are you saying
you only fabricated the case,

680
00:47:21,755 --> 00:47:23,840
and you are not involved in the murder?

681
00:47:24,841 --> 00:47:25,801
That's right.

682
00:47:25,884 --> 00:47:27,928
I found out after President Cha died.

683
00:47:30,013 --> 00:47:31,306
I, Noh Hwa-young,

684
00:47:31,932 --> 00:47:34,601
have not lived my life
for myself, even for a moment.

685
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:35,727
I served

686
00:47:35,811 --> 00:47:38,355
only the nation and the people.

687
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:42,234
The peace and goodwill
of this nation you're enjoying…

688
00:47:42,317 --> 00:47:43,944
Who do you think gave you those?

689
00:47:44,444 --> 00:47:47,155
Do you know what it's like
to live as a serviceperson

690
00:47:47,239 --> 00:47:51,285
in a country where the war
can break out anytime, even tomorrow?

691
00:47:52,286 --> 00:47:55,122
In order to protect
the military discipline,

692
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:57,791
I treated ranks and orders
like they were my life,

693
00:47:57,874 --> 00:48:00,669
and I tried my best
to train strong servicepeople.

694
00:48:01,253 --> 00:48:04,339
But is this what I get

695
00:48:04,423 --> 00:48:05,966
for all of that?

696
00:48:06,049 --> 00:48:09,052
That evil witch did all of these!

697
00:48:09,136 --> 00:48:11,555
Noh Hwa-young is truly an evil witch!

698
00:48:11,638 --> 00:48:12,889
You ordered me to do it!

699
00:48:12,973 --> 00:48:17,686
My life is ruined because of you!
You're the worst flaw in my life!

700
00:48:17,769 --> 00:48:21,815
-What? You served the country?
-That's enough! Order!

701
00:48:23,066 --> 00:48:24,234
Hey, Noh Hwa-young!

702
00:48:26,903 --> 00:48:29,156
The prosecution,
please request the sentencing.

703
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,242
The defendant has been committing

704
00:48:32,826 --> 00:48:34,578
all kinds of horrible crimes

705
00:48:34,661 --> 00:48:37,289
for the past 20 years
using her status as a serviceperson,

706
00:48:37,372 --> 00:48:39,499
and she's been concealing her crimes

707
00:48:39,583 --> 00:48:42,794
in meticulous and sly ways above rank.

708
00:48:43,503 --> 00:48:45,005
The defendant was

709
00:48:45,088 --> 00:48:48,008
an extremely proud serviceperson,

710
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:51,970
but she made herself collapse
due to her unconditional greed for power.

711
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:56,224
In the end, the military does not change
because servicepeople like her

712
00:48:56,308 --> 00:48:58,101
are in the military.

713
00:48:59,102 --> 00:49:00,312
The ranks

714
00:49:00,395 --> 00:49:02,064
and the orders

715
00:49:03,732 --> 00:49:06,526
must exist only for this nation,

716
00:49:07,444 --> 00:49:11,531
and they must never be used for
the personal purposes of an individual.

717
00:49:12,699 --> 00:49:16,078
Therefore, I,
the military prosecutor, request

718
00:49:16,161 --> 00:49:19,748
the death sentence for the defendant.

719
00:49:35,430 --> 00:49:38,266
Doctor, Mr. Noh Tae-nam just woke up.

720
00:49:50,612 --> 00:49:55,492
The court finds all charges brought up
by the prosecution guilty.

721
00:49:55,575 --> 00:49:59,454
Therefore, the court
sentences the verdict.

722
00:50:00,247 --> 00:50:01,289
The verdict.

723
00:50:02,416 --> 00:50:05,627
The court sentences
the defendant to death.

724
00:50:15,721 --> 00:50:17,597
Don't touch me.

725
00:50:18,390 --> 00:50:19,975
I'll walk on my own.

726
00:51:14,321 --> 00:51:17,657
I'll quit being a military prosecutor.

727
00:51:18,742 --> 00:51:19,826
What?

728
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:23,789
I will reveal everything I did
as the red-haired girl.

729
00:51:23,872 --> 00:51:26,041
Do you have to do that?

730
00:51:26,124 --> 00:51:28,335
-You only did that to criminals--
-Yes.

731
00:51:28,919 --> 00:51:30,378
I have to do that.

732
00:51:31,004 --> 00:51:34,466
I decided to do it from the start.
I'm prepared for this.

733
00:51:34,549 --> 00:51:36,426
I do not qualify

734
00:51:36,510 --> 00:51:39,846
to wear the prosecutor's robe anymore.

735
00:51:40,972 --> 00:51:41,807
Prosecutor Cha.

736
00:51:42,974 --> 00:51:44,267
Prosecutor Doh.

737
00:51:53,485 --> 00:51:55,612
-They're here!
-They're coming!

738
00:52:02,577 --> 00:52:04,162
As of today, I, Cha Woo-in,

739
00:52:04,246 --> 00:52:07,290
wish to resign from being
a military prosecutor of the 4th Division.

740
00:52:08,667 --> 00:52:12,087
I've been wearing a red wig

741
00:52:12,921 --> 00:52:16,925
and punishing criminals
who could not be punished by the law.

742
00:52:27,143 --> 00:52:29,145
ONE YEAR LATER

743
00:52:31,815 --> 00:52:33,316
My gosh!

744
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,360
This is killing me!

745
00:52:36,319 --> 00:52:38,989
Soo-kyung, just get a cesarean section,
as the doctor said!

746
00:52:39,072 --> 00:52:40,991
This is breaking my heart!

747
00:52:41,616 --> 00:52:44,369
I'm over 40, but I can still do it.

748
00:52:44,452 --> 00:52:47,581
I will give birth to my baby on my own!

749
00:52:52,085 --> 00:52:53,837
Prosecutor Doh!

750
00:52:53,920 --> 00:52:56,923
Is the office of justice
of the 4th Division doing well without me?

751
00:52:57,549 --> 00:52:58,550
Wait!

752
00:52:59,801 --> 00:53:00,969
Bae-man!

753
00:53:01,052 --> 00:53:03,930
Auntie! Auntie, cheer up!

754
00:53:10,186 --> 00:53:11,104
Thank you.

755
00:53:30,290 --> 00:53:31,333
What the…

756
00:53:33,335 --> 00:53:36,713
What's the point of locking them up
when they get released so fast?

757
00:53:37,297 --> 00:53:39,716
They reduced my sentencing
for being a model prisoner.

758
00:53:40,884 --> 00:53:44,638
Why is this country
so generous to economic criminals?

759
00:53:44,721 --> 00:53:45,639
I know, right?

760
00:53:46,348 --> 00:53:50,268
I didn't have bad intentions,
so it was taken into consideration.

761
00:53:50,977 --> 00:53:53,229
"Love the sinner, but hate the sin."

762
00:53:53,813 --> 00:53:55,690
That applies to this situation.

763
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:58,443
I paid for all of my crimes.

764
00:53:58,526 --> 00:54:00,904
You should have told me.
I could have bought tofu.

765
00:54:01,988 --> 00:54:02,822
No…

766
00:54:03,740 --> 00:54:05,951
How about we go
and have tofu soup with soju?

767
00:54:06,785 --> 00:54:08,370
That's too bad.

768
00:54:10,705 --> 00:54:12,165
I don't like tofu.

769
00:54:13,875 --> 00:54:15,085
Where are you going?

770
00:54:17,754 --> 00:54:19,589
I'm going back to the U.S. soon.

771
00:54:20,256 --> 00:54:22,217
I'm going to start over from the bottom,

772
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:24,844
because I finished giving IM
back to Woo-in.

773
00:54:27,389 --> 00:54:28,390
Bye.

774
00:54:31,893 --> 00:54:33,603
Woo-in is coming to Korea tomorrow.

775
00:54:39,067 --> 00:54:40,068
Have a safe trip back.

776
00:54:55,333 --> 00:54:57,168
The inmate refused to see you.

777
00:55:00,755 --> 00:55:01,673
Then…

778
00:55:02,382 --> 00:55:04,759
can you please deliver this to her?

779
00:55:12,517 --> 00:55:15,186
Mother. How are you doing?

780
00:55:15,895 --> 00:55:17,355
I'm doing fine.

781
00:55:18,231 --> 00:55:20,942
Bolt who you've never hugged

782
00:55:21,026 --> 00:55:23,903
and who was my only family…

783
00:55:23,987 --> 00:55:26,406
I sent him
to Military Prosecutor Doh Bae-man.

784
00:55:27,282 --> 00:55:31,911
I cried a lot after I sent him,
but I feel like I've matured a lot.

785
00:55:33,496 --> 00:55:38,126
I hope
that you are doing well in there, too.

786
00:55:39,586 --> 00:55:41,671
I don't know when it will be…

787
00:55:42,422 --> 00:55:44,799
but I want to see you someday.

788
00:55:45,717 --> 00:55:46,843
Mom.

789
00:56:11,993 --> 00:56:13,369
Where is it?

790
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:20,418
Woo-in.

791
00:56:22,253 --> 00:56:23,379
You…

792
00:56:24,547 --> 00:56:26,257
You came just in time.

793
00:56:27,884 --> 00:56:30,762
I'm glad
that I get to see you before I go.

794
00:56:36,976 --> 00:56:38,686
You went through a lot.

795
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:43,274
No.

796
00:56:44,317 --> 00:56:46,986
I hope you don't have to
get any more revenge now.

797
00:56:48,655 --> 00:56:50,198
And run IM well.

798
00:56:51,282 --> 00:56:52,242
I mean it.

799
00:56:52,951 --> 00:56:56,871
I bought lots of IM's stocks.
You have to do a good job.

800
00:56:56,955 --> 00:56:58,540
I'll be watching you.

801
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:02,877
You haven't changed at all
since I met you for the first time.

802
00:57:04,170 --> 00:57:05,797
Except for one thing.

803
00:57:16,349 --> 00:57:18,351
Now it's finally back to its true owner.

804
00:57:28,319 --> 00:57:31,823
You really are a great friend to me.

805
00:57:36,578 --> 00:57:37,662
I got to go.

806
00:57:38,746 --> 00:57:39,706
Okay.

807
00:57:40,415 --> 00:57:41,708
Contact me often.

808
00:57:41,791 --> 00:57:43,001
Okay.

809
00:58:07,817 --> 00:58:10,820
Noh Tae-nam gave
all of his shares to Woo-in.

810
00:58:33,468 --> 00:58:34,469
Bolt!

811
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:41,017
Thank you, Noh Tae-nam.

812
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:44,395
I know it wasn't easy for you
to decide to send Bolt to me.

813
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:46,022
My boy Bolt

814
00:58:46,105 --> 00:58:48,483
is the most loyal
and the bravest boy ever,

815
00:58:48,566 --> 00:58:50,485
so being a military dog suits him better.

816
00:58:51,319 --> 00:58:52,445
So,

817
00:58:52,529 --> 00:58:54,697
please take care of him.

818
00:58:55,281 --> 00:58:56,366
Well, sure.

819
00:58:58,993 --> 00:59:02,580
I heard you gave all of your shares
of IM to Cha Woo-in.

820
00:59:05,708 --> 00:59:08,211
Well, my mom gave me those, anyway.

821
00:59:08,294 --> 00:59:13,132
My mom lost everything,
so it would be wrong for me to keep those.

822
00:59:13,800 --> 00:59:16,261
Is she still refusing to see you?

823
00:59:18,888 --> 00:59:19,764
Yes.

824
00:59:20,682 --> 00:59:23,351
Well, I'm sure she'll see me someday.

825
00:59:24,143 --> 00:59:28,189
PRESIDENT CHA WOO-IN

826
01:00:06,227 --> 01:00:07,478
Dad?

827
01:00:10,064 --> 01:00:11,482
My daughter.

828
01:00:12,483 --> 01:00:14,319
It's been hard for you, right?

829
01:00:17,238 --> 01:00:18,990
Dad.

830
01:00:19,073 --> 01:00:20,617
You went through a lot.

831
01:00:22,910 --> 01:00:24,037
And,

832
01:00:26,080 --> 01:00:27,832
thank you, my daughter.

833
01:00:31,586 --> 01:00:32,879
If you sit in that chair,

834
01:00:34,714 --> 01:00:37,091
things are going to get harder.

835
01:00:38,926 --> 01:00:40,178
Can you do it?

836
01:00:41,179 --> 01:00:42,263
Yes.

837
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:45,391
I will do it.

838
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:48,227
Please watch me.

839
01:01:00,782 --> 01:01:02,742
President Cha, you have a guest.

840
01:01:02,825 --> 01:01:04,786
What? A guest?

841
01:01:04,869 --> 01:01:07,372
But I'm quite busy today.

842
01:01:08,206 --> 01:01:09,457
Who is it?

843
01:01:09,540 --> 01:01:12,210
She's from the office of justice
of the 4th Division.

844
01:01:13,461 --> 01:01:15,213
Shall I politely tell her to leave?

845
01:01:15,296 --> 01:01:19,092
No. Please cancel all of my
other schedules for today.

846
01:01:19,175 --> 01:01:21,094
Yes, ma'am. I'll bring her in.

847
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:26,933
Prosecutor Cha!

848
01:01:29,102 --> 01:01:31,938
I mean… President Cha.

849
01:01:32,772 --> 01:01:34,107
Subsection Chief Ahn!

850
01:01:34,857 --> 01:01:36,526
How have you been?

851
01:01:36,609 --> 01:01:39,237
Come on! You didn't even call us
all this time?

852
01:01:40,113 --> 01:01:42,532
And how can you look so dashing like this?

853
01:01:44,242 --> 01:01:46,244
How's Subsection Chief Yoon?

854
01:01:46,828 --> 01:01:48,162
He's still the same.

855
01:01:49,747 --> 01:01:53,209
By the way, aren't you curious
about Prosecutor Doh?

856
01:01:57,547 --> 01:02:00,967
Are you Prosecutor Doh Bae-man
who rejected the special promotion?

857
01:02:01,050 --> 01:02:02,635
Captain Doh Bae-man.

858
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:03,845
Yes, ma'am.

859
01:02:04,721 --> 01:02:06,264
What's the reason?

860
01:02:07,056 --> 01:02:09,726
All servicepeople want
to be in a high rank.

861
01:02:11,352 --> 01:02:13,938
I think military prosecutors
are the protectors of justice

862
01:02:14,021 --> 01:02:16,524
in the military
who can refuse ranks and orders.

863
01:02:16,607 --> 01:02:20,695
I wish to do a better job in carrying out
the duties the people gave me.

864
01:02:22,029 --> 01:02:26,117
And I still have
a lot of things left to do

865
01:02:26,200 --> 01:02:27,535
as a military prosecutor.

866
01:02:28,244 --> 01:02:31,247
You really are brave
like a Doberman, just as I heard.

867
01:02:32,165 --> 01:02:35,168
I will do my best
to command the 4th Division, too.

868
01:02:35,251 --> 01:02:36,753
Yes, ma'am!

869
01:02:36,836 --> 01:02:38,379
Salute!

870
01:02:48,848 --> 01:02:51,017
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

871
01:02:52,393 --> 01:02:54,228
-Goodbye.
-Okay, bye.

872
01:03:17,210 --> 01:03:18,377
Cha Woo-in.

873
01:03:18,461 --> 01:03:19,545
It's me.

874
01:03:20,546 --> 01:03:23,966
Wow, you still look good in your uniform.

875
01:03:27,553 --> 01:03:28,554
What the heck?

876
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:30,139
You said you were busy.

877
01:03:31,057 --> 01:03:34,811
You've become a totally different
person now, Prosecutor Cha.

878
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:36,687
I'm not a prosecutor anymore.

879
01:03:36,771 --> 01:03:38,189
I'm a civilian.

880
01:03:38,940 --> 01:03:40,858
Which means I'm not your subordinate.

881
01:03:42,944 --> 01:03:44,237
That's right.

882
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:45,655
You aren't.

883
01:03:47,156 --> 01:03:48,991
I got my revenge,

884
01:03:49,075 --> 01:03:50,827
got my company back,

885
01:03:51,619 --> 01:03:53,329
and met you again.

886
01:03:54,038 --> 01:03:56,582
So I'll make an offer you can't refuse.

887
01:04:02,713 --> 01:04:04,006
Anything.

888
01:05:27,465 --> 01:05:28,674
Doh Bae-man!

889
01:05:42,355 --> 01:05:43,522
THANK YOU FOR WATCHING
MILITARY PROSECUTOR DOBERMAN

890
01:05:43,606 --> 01:05:45,149
WE CHEER FOR THE SERVICEPEOPLE
OF REPUBLIC OF KOREA, SALUTE!

891
01:05:47,526 --> 01:05:52,531
Subtitle translation by: Hae-lim Lee

